<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Hardened Runtime entitlements — intentionally MINIMAL.

  Deliberately NOT present (and must never be added):
    * com.apple.security.network.client
        Keeping this absent is a second line of defence for the non-communication
        guarantee. (Note: without App Sandbox this does not hard-block sockets, but its
        absence is asserted by Scripts/audit-binary.sh.)
    * com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation
        Absence keeps library validation ON, preventing unsigned dylib injection that
        could bypass the non-communication guards.

  App Sandbox is intentionally NOT used: it would block Accessibility requests to other
  apps, which is rubyfree's core capability. We ship non-sandboxed + Hardened Runtime.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict/>
</plist>
